            <div class="title">Guide of Translator Mode</div>

            <h1><span>1</span>Current Regulator and Locale</h1>
            <p>After you click on the given link with a translator token, you will see at the top of website the "Translator Menu".</p>
            <p>But before you start you must be sure that current selected Regulator [1] (branch) and target Locale [2] (the language you planned to modify) are correct.</p>
            <img src="/img/png/00.jpg"></img>

            <h1><span>2</span>Translator Menu</h1>
            <br><b>Help</b> - This Guide of Translator Mode
            <br><b>Logout</b> - LogOut from Translator Mode
            <br><b>Apply</b> - Send all stored changes for a current Language
            <br><b>Apply All</b> - Send all stored changes for ALL Languages
            <br><b>Clear</b> - Clear all stored changes for a current Language
            <br><b>Clear All</b> - Clear all stored changes for ALL Languages
            <br><b>Edit</b> - Switch Editing Mode for a current Language
            <br><b>Edit Dynamics</b> - Move to the Dynamically Generated keys

            <img src="/img/gif/01.gif"></img>

            <h1><span>3</span>Clear All before start</h1>
            <p>Usually, when you did some corrections, you changes always stored in the local cache of you browser.</p>
            <p>Click on "Clear All" button before start each new session (session means a set of all you changes after you start and until you press "Apply" button for upload you changes to server).</p>
            <p>After click on "Clear All" the website page will reloaded and you can start.</p>
            <img src="/img/gif/02.gif"></img>

            <h1><span>4</span>"Edit" and "Stop edit" modes</h1>
            <p>When you see the "Edit" button it means the real edit mode is not active yet (you can't modify nothing).</p>
            <p>To activate editing mode simple click on the "Edit" button. Current website page will reload and you will see "Stop edit" button instead.</p>
            <p>When you see the "Stop edit" button it means now you are in the edit mode and you can modify anything (what is available to change).</p>
            <p>After you finish changes on the current page, switch off editing mode before you go to other page, and switch on the editing mode after new page load.</p>
            <img src="/img/gif/03.gif"></img>

            <h1><span>5</span>Editing Process</h1>
            <p>Before start editing better to clear all previous (already applied) changes. But if you was not click "Apply" button at previous editing session, then you should not click on the "Clear" or "Clear All" buttons, because you will lost all you changes which are not applied yet.</p>
            <p>When you previous changes was already applied, then click on "Clear" or "Clear All" buttons before start new editing session.</p>
            <p>Click on "Edit" button and wait for page reload. After done you will see the "Stop edit" button instead.</p>
            <p>Then, by click on some text, you will see the built-in editor, currently editable content background will fill by light red color.</p>
            <p>Inside light red box you can change content manually. And after you finish - click somewhere outside of red box (modified content will automatically store in the local cache of you browser, will marked on the page as "changed" and will fill by light blue color)</p>
            <p>If you see in some already modified by you (blue boxes on the page) wrong text, then click inside this blue box and then found at the bottom left corner of this box and click on the "REVERT" red button (to restore previous content before you changes).</p>
            <p>When you will done all expected changes on current page, then click on "Apply" button and then on "Stop edit".</p>
            <p>Now you will see current page in the non-editable mode but with you changes.</p>
            <p>You can repeat steps above for any other website pages.</p>
            <p>Only after you think you done (everything allready applied) you can click on "Logout" button. Then you translator session will done, translator token will delete, and you will not able to use Translator Interface using old link with deleted token.</p>
            <img src="/img/gif/04.gif"></img>

            <h1><span>6</span>What is "Edit Dynamics"?</h1>
            <p>Some website pages are include the programmatically created texts (or hided by default but apearred in some cases).</p>
            <p>Normally you cannot modify it, just because you don't see it on the page at all times.</p>
            <p>Table of "Dynamics" content is for arrange possibility to modify hidden texts.</p>
            <p>If page has hidden content, then at the bottom you can see the "Dynamically Generated keys" table.</p>
            <p>In this table you can see columns: "Key" (internal identifier), "English" (stored content in english locale) and "Current" (stored content in the current website locale which you see now).</p>
            <p>Content in the column "Current" you will able to modify (of course after switch to editing mode)</p>
            <p>So, after you click on "Edit Dynamics" button, current website page will just scrolling to the "Dynamically Generated keys" table.</p>
            <img src="/img/gif/05.gif"></img>
